HTML Lists
•	A list is a set of related items.
•	There are two types of lists:
o	Unordered Lists
o	Ordered Lists
Unordered Lists
•	Unordered Lists are used to present a collection of related items when sequence of items is not important.
Ex:
List of Fruits:
•	Grapes
•	Apples
•	Cherry
•	Banana
Syntax of Unordered List:
<ul>
  <li> item1 </li>
  <li> item2 </li>
</ul>
ul stands for Unordered List
li stands for List Item
Program for Unordered List:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
 <title> Unordered List </title>
</head>
<body>
<ul>
   <li> Apples </li>
   <li> Banana </li>
   <li> Cherry </li>
   <li> Grapes </li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>

Ordered Lists:
•	Ordered lists are used to display a list of items in a specific sequence, which are marked with numbers or letters.
•	By default, ordered list will be displayed with numbers.
•	Ordered lists can be displayed with:
o	Numbers  (1,2,3 …)
o	Uppercase letters (A,B,C, ….)
o	Lowercase letters( a, b, c, ….)
o	Uppercase Roman Numbers (I, II, III, IV, V, …)
o	Lowercase Roman Numbers (I, ii, iii, iv, v, …)
Syntax of Ordered List:
<ol>
    <li> item1 </li>
   <li> item2 </li>
</ol>
ol stands for Ordered List
li stands for List Item
Program for Ordered List:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title> Ordered List </title>
</head>
<body>
<ol>
    <li> C#.net </li>
    <li> ASP.net </li>
    <li> ADO.net </li>
    <li> SQL Server </li>
    <li> MVC </li>
</ol>
</body>
</html>
For Uppercase ordered list:   <ol type="A">
For Lowercase ordered list:  <ol type="a">
For Uppercase Roman Numbered Ordered List: <ol type="I">
For Lowercase Roman Numbered Ordered List: <ol type="i">
HTML Forms
•	HTML form is used to collect user input.
•	The examples of user input:
o	First Name
o	Last Name
o	Gender
o	Date Of Birth
o	Age
o	Email ID
o	Phone Number
o	Address etc….
•	To collect the user input, the following input types will be used:
o	Label
o	Textbox
o	Checkbox
o	Radio Button
o	Buttons
o	List box etc….
Label: Label is used to tell the user to enter what input.
 
Syntax of Label:
<label> Label Text </label>
Ex:
<label> First Name </label>

Textbox: Textbox is used to take input from the user.
Syntax of Textbox:
<input type="text">
Button: Button is used to perform the action or operation such as submit operation, insert operation, update operation, delete operation etc….
Syntax of button:
<input type="submit">
Textarea: Textarea is used to input multiple lines of text.
Syntax of textarea:
<textarea rows=”number of rows” cols=”Number of columns”></textarea>


Ex:
<label> Address </label>
<textarea rows=”5” cols=”20”></textarea>
Program:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Form  Example </title>
</head>
<body>
<form>
   <label> First Name </label>
   <input type="text"><br><br>   
   <label> Last Name </label>
   <input type="text"><br><br>
    <label> Address </label><br>
    <textarea rows="5" cols="20"></textarea> <br><br>
   <input type="submit">
</form>
</body>
</html>
Homework
Interview Questions:
1.	What is Unordered list?
2.	What is Ordered List and write the difference between Ordered list and unordered list?
3.	What is a Form?
4.	Explain the following input controls:
a.	Label
b.	Textbox
c.	Textarea
d.	Button
Tasks
Task1: Write a HTML program to create both ordered and unordered lists
Task2: Write a HTML program to take input: Emp ID, Emp Name and Emp Salary 
Task3: Write a HTML program to take input: Product ID, product name, product price



























